  "2026-07-19T12:41:28.445Z",maintainer-agent,"Evidence: --add-ac/--remove-ac are wired through update/update-many, contracts, MCP, completions, docs, previews, conflict guards, and exact-match warnings. Linked 204-test gate passes; full coverage is 100/100/100/100; manual built-CLI acceptance produced base criterion; cli criterion."
  "2026-07-19T12:50:16.361Z",maintainer-agent,"Release-gate evidence: pnpm release:gates completed build, typecheck, docs/skills, static quality, package boundary, token budget, 5,963 tests with exact 100/100/100/100 coverage, version/sync, secret scan, packed-package smoke, and package-first dogfood successfully. The aggregate command stopped only at its intentional Greptile stage because Greptile requires a committed diff against main; the local commit will be reviewed before push."
  "2026-07-19T13:09:32.397Z",maintainer-agent,"Greptile pre-push review 078e4d2f-271c-42de-9de5-665f5d4ad9c7 found two actionable gaps. Fixed bulk unmatched --remove-ac reporting across dry-run, all-no-op apply, and mixed updated/skipped rows; documented the semicolon criterion-boundary constraint in public JSDoc, CLI help, command/agent docs, and SDK docs. Focused 99 tests, static quality, contracts, and full 5,963-test 100/100/100/100 coverage pass after the fix."
  "2026-07-19T13:16:27.198Z",maintainer-agent,"Greptile amended-head review 40307c95-e203-49c2-9a2c-5ad83062bcd0 returned confidence 5/5, confirmed both prior findings resolved, and produced no review comments. Applied its remaining non-blocking consistency nit so register-mutation help also labels additive acceptance criteria semicolon-free."
notes[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-19T11:59:56.829Z",maintainer-agent,"Implemented with full new-flag checklist: --add-ac/--remove-ac on pm update AND pm update-many. Core helpers splitAcceptanceCriteria/applyAcceptanceCriteriaMutations in core/item/parse.ts (criteria = \"; \"-separated segments; adds append in argv order + dedupe exact trimmed text; removals exact trimmed match; unmatched removals surface remove_ac_unmatched:<text> warnings — never a silent no-op). Additive mutation runs AFTER the scalar --ac replace so composition uses the replaced base. Guards: --unset ac × --add-ac/--remove-ac rejected; ownership-dependency-bypass scope rejects both; command_option_policy marks acceptanceCriteria for additive forms. update-many gets a composed preview plan (an --add-ac-only bulk run is actionable, not a skip; scalar+additive plans deduped into one acceptance_criteria change). Wiring: UPDATE_COMMANDER_OPTION_REGISTRATION_CONTRACTS (+snake aliases), registration-helpers, update-many hand-registered options + hidden aliases, UPDATE/UPDATE_MANY flag contracts, MCP tool-option-contracts (addAc/removeAc repeatable) + parameter tables + descriptions, zsh/fish completions for update+update-many, docs COMMANDS.md + AGENT_GUIDE.md, contracts snapshot regenerated after build. Manual verify: add/dedupe/remove/unmatched-warning all correct."
